cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.HC 

This paper proposes a learning algorithm that leverages intrinsic motivations and natural language interactions with a social partner to learn its own reward function and engage in autonomous goal exploration. The paper involves robotics and language grounding, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the paper involves language interactions and learning algorithms. The paper also involves reinforcement learning and autonomous agents, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper involves human-robot interactions, which suggests that it could belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
